==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Clepe
<hw>Clepe</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To make appeal; to cry out.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Wandering in woe, and to the heavens on high⟦br⟧
<qex>Cleping</qex> for vengeance of this treachery.</q> <rj><qau>Mir.
for Mag.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Clepsine</ent>⟦br⟧
